{"id":"RF-171","entityId":"95-346","jiraId":null,"field":[{"name":"projectShortName","value":"RF"},{"name":"numberInProject","value":"171"},{"name":"summary","value":"when principal is true, should never set principalId1 > 0 and principalId2 > 0"},{"name":"description","value":"
In gedcom 4035, Margie Nell Lunsford has a BIRT event where principal=true, principalId1>0 and principalId2>0. This is incorrect. PrincipalId1 and principalId2 refer to other principals in the event. They should only be set for family events like MARR, where principalId1 points to the other spouse. They should never be set for individual events like BIRT. And you should never set principalId2 in your code at all.

Same goes for Debbie Barnes, John Wayne Kinley, J T Lunsford, and "Pickett".

Can you fix this?
